        <p data-uuid="49e97c4a93f440908fa7cf8bbfc88ec0">The Taino lived in small farming communities. In his journal, Columbus wrote that the Taino were “so generous . . . that no one would believe it who has not seen it.” However, Columbus and his crew were not interested in Taino culture, but in gold. After three months of exploring, looking for gold, and collecting exotic plants and animals, Columbus returned to Spain.<br />
        </p>
        <p data-uuid="c532555b525d40b0a5611d337b0f0d40"> Columbus made three more journeys to the Americas during his lifetime. In 1504 he returned to Spain in poor health. Columbus died two years later, still believing that he had reached Asia.</p>
